      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OKEY (5) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by 2.25 lengths at this track in a handy 17.51 beating Park Key Paw. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Well placed and will be tough to beat. KIARNI BOLT (3) flew the lids from the middle with a slick turn of foot before finishing second (22.48) and beaten 8 lengths over 400m at Maitland. Deserves a win and gets his chance. RIPPED RACCOON (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (29.00) last time in a NG at Casino. Is yet to taste defeat at this course. Key player if finds best. CATCH THE TIGER (1) placed here at this trip last start - cannot be ignored.",
